<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_GP10_InteriorDecoratorCareer" s="269146">
  <T n="category">269186<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_DreamHomeDecorator--></T>
  <T n="name">0x2866FEF3<!--String: "Interior Decorator Career"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f2</T>
      <T n="text">0x699C431A<!--String: "Tired of your neighbors' terrible décor? Wish you could share your impeccable taste with the world? Then it’s time to join the Interior Decorator Career! Interior Decorators bring their Client’s renovation dreams to life one gig at a time. Once you join the Career, use the Career Panel to Look for Gigs."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f1</T>
      <T n="text">0xB454A018<!--String: "When it's time to start a gig, you’ll be prompted to make a choice. You can either send Sims off by themselves or you can go with them. If you choose to go with them, you will travel to meet the Client at the lot in need of renovation. Once there, you can direct your Sim through the renovation process by following the Gig Tasks in the Career Panel."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f0</T>
      <T n="text">0x2F254B82<!--String: "Getting to know the Client can make the difference between a decent renovation and a great one. Sims can have many different Likes and Dislikes, but they’ll focus on a few preferences for a gig. More experienced Interior Decorators can learn preferences quickly and suggest different colors or décor. If you’re not feeling chatty, you can send the Client away and get right to work."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f7</T>
      <T n="text">0x8B7E0FDA<!--String: "You’ll need to document the renovation process by taking Before and After Photos. You can take photos from your phone, camera, or by clicking on the ground where you want to take the shot. Check out the Taking The Perfect Decorator Picture Lesson to learn more."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f6</T>
      <T n="text">0x93729382<!--String: "Enter Build Mode to start making renovations. The Gig Information Panel displays the Client’s budget, preferences, and any requirements or restrictions. You can click on discovered preferences to quickly see relevant objects."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f5</T>
      <T n="text">0x6158D38<!--String: "Some gigs require you to add an entire room or level. With these gigs, you can only add objects to the added tiles. For renovation gigs, you can add objects anywhere, but can't move the existing walls or floors. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_7.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84f4</T>
      <T n="text">0xF9E1772F<!--String: "Once you’re happy with the renovations, it’s time to call the Client back. You’ll be prompted to select the photos you want to showcase and decide how to handle the Reveal. You can either host the Reveal personally or leave it to the Client to check out on their own time."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_8.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84fb</T>
      <T n="text">0x12E9288B<!--String: "Hosting the Reveal lets you show off the new space and see how the Client really feels. After looking around, Clients will be ready to share their Final Verdict. Everyone wants to be heard, and even an upset Client will appreciate the effort."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP10\UI\Lessons\Career_Lesson_9.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4967007ab60c84fa</T>
      <T n="text">0x62896E5F<!--String: "Each successful gig brings you closer to the top! Gain experience to access a wider variety of gigs. Interior Decorators not only need to manage their Career Performance (just like other Careers), but also their Professional Reputation. Professional Reputation can open the door to even more opportunities, whether that’s a second chance from a disgruntled Client or attention from the Dream Home Decorator Network."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
</I>